BFN 

  [Excerpt] Geneva, 6 Jun (TANJUG) -- The republic of Srpska 
delegation met Yasushi Akashi, UN special envoy for the former 
Yugoslavia, this afternoon in the Palace of Nations. The 
delegation informed him about its criticisms and suggestions 
regarding a draft document on a general cease-fire in the former 
Yugoslav Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina. In addition to its 
general commitment to a lasting cessation of hostilities, the 
Serbian delegation also voiced some technical criticism 
regarding the issue of the corridor [linking Serbia with 
occupied areas in Croatia and Bosnia-Herzegovina], TANJUG 
learned from sources within the Serbian delegation. [passage 
omitted] 

